metadata.name: Flume #238
metadata.description:
Flume are infinitely flowing digital bodies of water.
The flow of Flumes can range from slow and gentle, creating small ripples and eddies, to fast and turbulent, carving its way through the inner workings of your computer screen. 
The color, clarity, and viscosity of the water can also vary.

This is the culmination of my collection Flume, an exploration into On-Chain art on Ethereum, https://etherscan.io/address/0x1fa23513825f952afca07a603ac3f312ebee4ca9

These pieces were all created in p5js.

- Andrew

metadata.name: Misty Harmony #126
metadata.description:
Floating cubes in a misty fog in harmony, each created with a unique color palette and five different angles to add an extra layer of depth and beauty to the composition.
This is the second collaboration between us. Get ready for more exciting works in the near future!

Features:
Five different angles, including isometric and more
13 captivating color palettes
4 different background colors
4 different background textures

-- Created in P5JS --

Open and Download For High Quality
